<TITLE> Work jointly to overcome crises: Khaleda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 9 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia has asked all to work jointly to overcome the current crises of the country. "Numerous problems have been created in the country in the last two years. To get over them we have to work jointly irrespective of cast and creed," Khaleda said to reporters on Tuesday after exchanging Eid greetings with people from across the social spectrum at Eskaton Ladies' Club. "We want to bring welfare to the country and its people." The former prime minister said her party would disclose election manifesto on Dec. 13. "The parliamentary election is going to be held on Dec. 29. We hope the government will lift the state of emergency soon so that people will cast their ballot fearlessly in a joyful environment." Khaleda said the country slipped back in the last two years. "People have gone starving. We hope an elected government will take up strong action in future," she said. Earlier the BNP chief exchanged Eid greetings with diplomats and party men and ordinary people. The guests were treated to sweets and delicacies on the occasion. b
